Your event handler (`handleChange`) is [destructuring][1] the event object, and trying to extract a property called `event` from it, which doesn&#39;t exist.

You need to use the event object directly instead:

    handleChange(event) {
      this.setState({
        [event.target.name]: event.target.value
      });
    }


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Destructuring_assignment

